text: Wenche Kvamme (19 June 1950 – 9 March 2019) was a Norwegian singer and actress. She was born in Bergen, Norway. She began her stage career at Nationaltheatret in 1977. She was appointed at the Bergen theatre Den Nationale Scene in 1978. She was best known for her roles in television shows include (1991), (1996–2000), and (2002–2003).
